<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="frightened-adj">frightened <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'fraɪtnd/    美 /'fraɪtnd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>受惊的；害怕的：</strong></h4>
<p>afraid; feeling; fear :</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Frightened children were calling for their mothers.
受到惊吓的孩子们呼喊着找妈妈。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don't be frightened. We're not going to hurt you.
别害怕，我们不会伤害你的。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>be frightened of (doing) sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Are you frightened of thunder? 
你害怕打雷吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I'm frightened of walking home alone at midnight.
我害怕深更半夜独自走回家。</p></div></div>